Steps in installing tar.gz file
1. Extract the file
2. Move extracted file to the Home directory
3. Open the extracted folder and open terminal
4. then type this into the terminal: ln -s 'Name of the software' ~/Desktop/ (This will add shortcut to your Desktop)


cd 'folder name'                   -> Move to the directory
cd ..                              -> Back to previos directory  
mkdir 'folder name'                -> Add folder
sudo rm -r 'filename'              -> Remove file or folder
cp 'file name' ~/Desktop/          -> Pin to Desktop
clear                              -> Clear the terminal
ln -s [target_path] [link_name]    -> Create a symbolic link to Desktop
